# D365 F&O Data Access

Microsoft source: [Transactional integrity](https://learn.microsoft.com/dynamics365/fin-ops-core/dev-itpro/dev-ref/xpp-data/xpp-transaction)

## Core rules

- `select forUpdate` before every update or delete
- Mutate in the **same TTS scope** as `forUpdate`
- Set-based ops over row-by-row loops for bulk work
- Joins over N+1 nested while-select
- Catch `UpdateConflict` / `Deadlock` with explicit type + `retry`

## Scenarios and recommendations

### Single-record update in service or CoC

**Recommend:** `ttsbegin` → `select forupdate` → mutate → `update()` → `ttscommit`; null-check buffer.

**Avoid:** Update without `forUpdate`; `doUpdate()`.

### Bulk update (thousands+ rows)

**Recommend:** `update_recordset` or chunked loops with **short TTS** per chunk; validate with Trace Parser.

**Avoid:** One `ttsbegin` around entire `while select` loop.

### Staging import / high-volume insert

**Recommend:** `RecordInsertList`, `insert_recordset`, or DMF entity — match volume to pattern.

**Avoid:** Row-by-row `insert()` inside tight loop without batching.

### Read-only inquiry / report prep

**Recommend:** Single query with joins; use field lists on large tables where appropriate.

**Avoid:** `forUpdate` on read-only paths; nested selects in loop (N+1).

### Concurrent updates (two users/processes)

**Recommend:** Catch `Exception::UpdateConflict` outside inner TTS or use `retry` when `appl.ttsLevel() == 0`.

**Avoid:** Swallowing exceptions; infinite retry without limit.

### Custom data entity for integration

**Recommend:** Built-in entity when sufficient; **custom entity** for high-volume/low-latency; normalize source tables.

**Avoid:** Redundant copy tables; entity without correct security integration mode.

## forUpdate example

```xpp
// BAD
ttsbegin;
select custTable where custTable.AccountNum == _accountNum;
custTable.CreditMax = 5000;
custTable.update();
ttscommit;

// GOOD
ttsbegin;
select forupdate custTable where custTable.AccountNum == _accountNum;
if (custTable) { custTable.CreditMax = 5000; custTable.update(); }
ttscommit;
```

